{"id":219,"url":"http:\/\/publications.newberry.org\/transcription\/mms-transcribe\/api\/items\/219","public":true,"featured":false,"added":"2017-12-07T21:31:27+00:00","modified":"2019-11-22T15:08:37+00:00","item_type":null,"collection":{"id":15,"url":"http:\/\/publications.newberry.org\/transcription\/mms-transcribe\/api\/collections\/15","resource":"collections"},"owner":{"id":1,"url":"http:\/\/publications.newberry.org\/transcription\/mms-transcribe\/api\/users\/1","resource":"users"},"files":{"count":187,"url":"http:\/\/publications.newberry.org\/transcription\/mms-transcribe\/api\/files?item=219","resource":"files"},"tags":[],"element_texts":[{"html":false,"text":"Hannah Hayden letters, 1806-1866","element_set":{"id":1,"url":"http:\/\/publications.newberry.org\/transcription\/mms-transcribe\/api\/element_sets\/1","name":"Dublin Core","resource":"element_sets"},"element":{"id":50,"url":"http:\/\/publications.newberry.org\/transcription\/mms-transcribe\/api\/elements\/50","name":"Title","resource":"elements"}},{"html":true,"text":"Hannah Hayden was born in Windsor, Connecticut, in 1778, and moved with her husband Hezekiah to Hartwick, Otsego County, New York in 1806, and then to Springfield, New York, in 1811. In both towns they ran saw mills. The Haydens had twelve children, several of whom died in infancy. Both Hannah and Hezekiah died in 1823.<br \/><br \/>This collection is composed mainly of letters written by Hannah Hayden from Hartwick and Springfield, Otsego County, New York, to her parents and siblings in Windsor, Connecticut, which discuss the details of everyday life: births, deaths, accidents, sicknesses, meetings, etc. The letters are pasted into a Jackson, Michigan general store receipt book, dated 1845-1847.<br \/><br \/>The correspondence, supplemented by a few other family letters, was compiled by son Henry A. Hayden in 1875. <a href=\"https:\/\/i-share.carli.illinois.edu\/nby\/cgi-bin\/Pwebrecon.cgi?DB=local&amp;v1=1&amp;BBRecID=822984\" target=